### getSETCCInGPR() {#a8e246c3623a788877f0b8c90233e7d24}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>SDValue anonymous&#95;namespace&#123;PPCISelDAGToDAG.cpp&#125;::IntegerCompareEliminator::getSETCCInGPR (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sdvalue">SDValue</a> Compare, SetccInGPROpts ConvOpts)</>}>
Returns an equivalent of a SETCC node but with the result the same width as the inputs.

This can also be used for SELECT&#95;CC if either the true or false values is a power of two while the other is zero.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/powerpc/ppciseldagtodag-cpp/#l02921">2921</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/powerpc/ppciseldagtodag-cpp">PPCISelDAGToDAG.cpp</a>.

### signExtendInputIfNeeded() {#a8cb666cab1615585574d98a85a1e1a55}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>SDValue anonymous&#95;namespace&#123;PPCISelDAGToDAG.cpp&#125;::IntegerCompareEliminator::signExtendInputIfNeeded (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sdvalue">SDValue</a> Input)</>}>
If the value isn&#39;t guaranteed to be sign-extended to 64-bits, extend it.

Otherwise just reinterpret it as a 64-bit value. Useful when emitting comparison code for 32-bit values without using the compare instruction (which only considers the lower 32-bits).

### zeroExtendInputIfNeeded() {#ad3df2f4ccab05de99625ca6bfe140a3d}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>SDValue anonymous&#95;namespace&#123;PPCISelDAGToDAG.cpp&#125;::IntegerCompareEliminator::zeroExtendInputIfNeeded (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sdvalue">SDValue</a> Input)</>}>
If the value isn&#39;t guaranteed to be zero-extended to 64-bits, extend it.

Otherwise just reinterpret it as a 64-bit value. Useful when emitting comparison code for 32-bit values without using the compare instruction (which only considers the lower 32-bits).
